title: [Whistler's Pass, Grassy Field]
description: The giant conifers begin to thin as the trail continues its descent.  An owl's call can be heard in the distance.  Patches of grass spill across the mountainside, interrupted only by a mound of small stones just off the trail.  Slight breezes blow puffs of rolling mist through the trail.
